
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-bonica-lsr-ip-flexalgo-01.txt'>
    <title>"IGP Flexible Algorithms (Flex-Algorithm) In IP Networks", William Britto, Shraddha Hegde, Parag Kaneriya, Rejesh Shetty, Ron Bonica, Peter Psenak</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-bonica-lsr-ip-flexalgo-01.txt</link>
    <description>An IGP Flexible Algorithm (Flex-Algorithm) allows IGP to compute constraint-based paths.  As currently defined, IGP Flex-Algorithm is used with Segment Routing (SR) data planes - SR MPLS and SRv6. Therefore, Flex-Algorithm cannot be deployed in the absence of SR.  This document extends IGP Flex-Algorithm, so that it can be used for regular IPv4 and IPv6 prefixes.  This allows Flex-Algorithm to be deployed in any IP network, even in the absence of SR.</description>
    <dc:date>2020-11-15T08:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
